review_title: Honestly- there is no Snail & Slug bait... only one designed to kill!
review_text: Have tried so-called organic Snail & Slug "bait" which is absolutely BS! These are nothing more than mineral salts which kill snails and slugs much the way that "salt" (sodium chloride) kills them by literally draining their predominantly mucous-membrane bodies of moisture. In other words they suffer a death similar to the horror movie (I will not mention the name here) where a person was drained completely of bodily fluids in a matter of seconds like some kind of Vampire attack.Metaldehyde which is the primary "snail & slug" killer ingredient may be toxic to any mammal ingesting it should applied with a product such as "Critter Out" or other Dog, Cat, Rat etc. repellent as pets may find the Corrys pellets a bit appetizing.This has been the most effective way to control Mollusca species! Of course extra care must be taken if there are pets with access to the treated area! Repellants will definitely help!At least one product promoted as "Snail Bait" is actually most desirable by mammals. I have applied what should have been sufficient to kill any snails or slugs coming in contact only to find almost all the granules gone! Iron sulfate which is the primary ingredient ends up being little more than a "fertilizer"...especially with regular watering.I advise: Apply this product with care! Although snails and slugs can be incredibly TOXIC to the garden Metaldehyde products can end up very toxic to our pets and wildlife.
